[[ Family 
<taxonomicName family="Cirrhitidae" pageNumber="1" rank="family">Cirrhitidae</taxonomicName>
]]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="1">
The perciform fish family 
<taxonomicName family="Cirrhitidae" pageNumber="1" rank="family">Cirrhitidae</taxonomicName>
is characterized by having 14 pectoral rays, the lower 5 to 7 unbranched and enlarged with the membranes deeply incised; a single dorsal fin of X spines and 11 to 17 soft rays, the fin notched between the spinous and soft portions; membrane at dorsal spine tips with one to several cirri; anal rays III,5-7; 15 principal caudal rays; pelvic rays I,5; opercular spines 2; a fringe of cirri on posterior edge of anterior nostril; margin of preopercle serrate, though often only on upper half (number of serrae increase with age); scales cycloid; gill membranes broadly joined, with a free fold across throat; no swimbladder; 6 branchiostegal rays; and 26 vertebrae. Except for the presence or absence of palatine teeth and except for the reduced size of the canines in the monotypic genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:9A5FCAE1-60DB-400B-BFD8-ED47AE93C254" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Oxycirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Oxycirrhites Bleeker 1857:39" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Oxycirrhites</taxonomicName>
, the dentition is essentially the same for all species: an outer row of small incurved canines, the largest in upper jaw at the front, and the largest in the lower jaw as 2 to 4 recurved canines nearly half way back in jaw; a broad dense inner band of villiform teeth at front of jaws, continuing progressively narrower posteriorly in upper jaw; a narrow V-shaped band of small teeth on the vomer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="2">
The 
<taxonomicName family="Cirrhitidae" pageNumber="2" rank="family">Cirrhitidae</taxonomicName>
is primarily an Indo-Pacific family, with only three of the 33 species occurring in the Atlantic, and only three in the eastern Pacific (two of which are also wideranging in the Indo-Pacific). Most are found in shallow water on coral reefs or rocky substrata, often in areas exposed to surge. When in a surgy area, they use their thickened lower pectoral rays to wedge themselves in place. 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cyprinocirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="polyactis">Cyprinocirrhites polyactis</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:87C7BC39-0FA3-4417-B201-74341F8AF192" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Oxycirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Oxycirrhites typus Bleeker 1857:40" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="typus">Oxycirrhites typus</taxonomicName>
are exceptions in their usual occurrence in 20-100 m. Cirrhitids feed mainly on benthic crustaceans, occasionally on small fishes. 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cyprinocirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="polyactis">C. polyactis</taxonomicName>
feeds well above the substratum on zooplankton, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:87C7BC39-0FA3-4417-B201-74341F8AF192" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Oxycirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Oxycirrhites typus Bleeker 1857:40" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="typus">O. typus</taxonomicName>
makes short forays into the water column for the larger animals of the zooplankton. At least some of the species (and likely all) are protogynous hermaphrodites (Sadovy &amp; Donaldson 1995).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="2">
The generic classification of the 
<taxonomicName family="Cirrhitidae" pageNumber="2" rank="family">Cirrhitidae</taxonomicName>
has a long and confused history which is summarized here:
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="2">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Günther">Guenther</normalizedToken>
(1860) recognized eight genera in the family, only three of which remain in the 
<taxonomicName family="Cirrhitidae" pageNumber="2" rank="family">Cirrhitidae</taxonomicName>
today: 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
Cirrhitus 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Lacepède">Lacepede</normalizedToken>
</taxonomicName>
(which 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Günther">Guenther</normalizedToken>
and most early authors misspelled 
<taxonomicName authority="Lacepède, 1803" authorityName="Lacepède" authorityYear="1803" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cirrhites</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A7B81F0C-1F8D-4339-A46A-3F2F625784D3" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cirrhitichthys Bleeker 1857:3, 39" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cirrhitichthys Bleeker</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:9A5FCAE1-60DB-400B-BFD8-ED47AE93C254" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Oxycirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Oxycirrhites Bleeker 1857:39" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Oxycirrhites Bleeker</taxonomicName>
. The other five genera are now classified in the families Cheilodactylidae and Chironemidae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="2">
Gill (1862) proposed the genera 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:6AD3621E-4DC7-4F31-A629-D987B190847D" authority="Gill, 1862" authorityName="Gill" authorityYear="1862" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cirrhitopsis Gill 1862:109" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cirrhitopsis</taxonomicName>
for 
<taxonomicName authority="Lacepède, 1803" authorityName="Lacepède" authorityYear="1803" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aureus">Cirrhites aureus Temminck and Schlegel</taxonomicName>
from Japan and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A7B68FE2-7E5D-4D15-BFA4-EE2E8BD8F54C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Amblycirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Amblycirrhitus Gill 1862:105" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Amblycirrhitus</taxonomicName>
for 
<taxonomicName authority="Lacepède, 1803" authorityName="Lacepède" authorityYear="1803" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fasciatus">Cirrhites fasciatus Cuvier (1829)</taxonomicName>
for which the type locality was given as 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pondichéry">Pondichery</normalizedToken>
, India.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="2">
Castelnau (1873) described 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:68D568EE-EDBF-4AC4-BE6C-33C431C86417" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Neocirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Neocirrhites armatus Castelnau 1873:101" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="armatus">Neocirrhites armatus</taxonomicName>
as a new genus and species from northeastern Australia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="2">
Bleeker (1875) treated five genera in the family for the East Indian region, adding 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A7B68FE2-7E5D-4D15-BFA4-EE2E8BD8F54C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Amblycirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Amblycirrhitus Gill 1862:105" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Amblycirrhitus Gill</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Paracirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Paracirrhites Bleeker</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="2">
Steindachner &amp; 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Döderlein">Doederlein</normalizedToken>
(1884) described 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:D6D47312-320D-435B-8DEE-6358F0B05CDC" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Paracirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Paracirrhites japonicus Steindachner 1883:25" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="japonicus">Paracirrhites japonicus</taxonomicName>
as a new genus and species from Japan. Noting that their 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:444182CC-9D9C-4C0C-9E68-4499A1BFF2A6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Paracirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Paracirrhites Steindachner 1883:25" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Paracirrhites</taxonomicName>
was preoccupied by 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Paracirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Paracirrhites Bleeker</taxonomicName>
, Jordan in Jordan &amp; Herre (1907) proposed the replacement name 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:2F6B48D5-B8C9-49E2-9393-87E1181F30DA" authority="Jordan, 1907" authorityName="Jordan" authorityYear="1907" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Isobuna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Isobuna Jordan 1907:158" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Isobuna</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="2">
Jenkins (1903) described 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:5BF2B80F-9DD4-43F0-822F-2E04167F332E" authority="Jenkins, 1903" authorityName="Jenkins" authorityYear="1903" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitoidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cirrhitoidea bimacula Jenkins 1903:489" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bimacula">Cirrhitoidea bimacula</taxonomicName>
as a new genus and species from the Hawaiian Islands, unaware that 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A7B68FE2-7E5D-4D15-BFA4-EE2E8BD8F54C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Amblycirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Amblycirrhitus Gill 1862:105" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Amblycirrhitus</taxonomicName>
was available for 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:5BF2B80F-9DD4-43F0-822F-2E04167F332E" authority="Jenkins, 1903" authorityName="Jenkins" authorityYear="1903" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitoidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cirrhitoidea bimacula Jenkins 1903:489" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bimacula">bimacula</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="2">
Tanaka (1917) created the genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:C7E5D36A-EA54-4B8C-8AF3-D40CB52A0CC6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cyprinocirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cyprinocirrhites Tanaka 1917:269" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cyprinocirrhites</taxonomicName>
for 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:C63C7CF8-5D08-4D7C-88D4-EABC81873844" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cirrhitichthys polyactis Bleeker 1874:16" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="polyactis">Cirrhitichthys polyactis Bleeker</taxonomicName>
, surprisingly not named earlier.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="2">
Mowbray in Breder (1927) described 
<taxonomicName authority="Mowbray, 1927" authorityName="Mowbray" authorityYear="1927" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Pseudocirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pinos">Pseudocirrhites pinos</taxonomicName>
as a new genus and species from the Isle of Pines, Cuba.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="2">
Fowler (1938) proposed the new genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:4F50B9C7-080F-4BE8-89C1-F7AC756414F2" authority="Fowler, 1938" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1938" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Acanthocirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Acanthocirrhitus Fowler 1938:50" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Acanthocirrhitus</taxonomicName>
for 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oxycephalus">Cirrhitus oxycephalus Bleeker</taxonomicName>
. Realizing that 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fasciatus">Cirrhitus fasciatus Cuvier</taxonomicName>
is preoccupied by 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fasciatus">C. fasciatus Bennett (1828)</taxonomicName>
, he provided a replacement name, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:90FD1EF3-9693-49BF-9BE7-6F1701307C7D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Amblycirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Amblycirrhitus indicus Fowler 1938:49" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="indicus">Amblycirrhitus indicus</taxonomicName>
. Randall (2001) has shown that Cuvier’s 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fasciatus">C. fasciatus</taxonomicName>
is a specimen of the Atlantic 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Amblycirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pinos">Amblycirrhitus pinos (Mowbray)</taxonomicName>
, and the type locality of India for 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fasciatus">fasciatus</taxonomicName>
is a locality error for the Atlantic.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="2">
Schultz (1943) mistakenly relegated 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:C7E5D36A-EA54-4B8C-8AF3-D40CB52A0CC6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cyprinocirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cyprinocirrhites Tanaka 1917:269" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cyprinocirrhites</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CC926BD0-C0C7-4941-87D0-54080B379A74" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Neocirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Neocirrhites Castelnau 1873:101" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Neocirrhites</taxonomicName>
to the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A7B81F0C-1F8D-4339-A46A-3F2F625784D3" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cirrhitichthys Bleeker 1857:3, 39" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cirrhitichthys</taxonomicName>
. He described 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:610A9D36-A6BE-46D2-9742-4B032894253B" authority="Schultz, 1943" authorityName="Schultz" authorityYear="1943" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Hughichthys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hughichthys Schultz 1943:131, 136" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hughichthys</taxonomicName>
as a new genus for 
<taxonomicName authority="Lacepède, 1803" authorityName="Lacepède" authorityYear="1803" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="melanotus">
Cirrhites melanotus 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Günther">Guenther</normalizedToken>
</taxonomicName>
, later shown to be a synonym of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:68D568EE-EDBF-4AC4-BE6C-33C431C86417" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Neocirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Neocirrhites armatus Castelnau 1873:101" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="armatus">Neocirrhites armatus Castelnau</taxonomicName>
. He then placed 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3C44979F-8863-4A9F-8276-923CD87238D8" authority="Jenkins, 1903" authorityName="Jenkins" authorityYear="1903" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitoidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cirrhitoidea Jenkins 1903:489" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cirrhitoidea</taxonomicName>
in the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Paracirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Paracirrhites</taxonomicName>
and classified 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:5BF2B80F-9DD4-43F0-822F-2E04167F332E" authority="Jenkins, 1903" authorityName="Jenkins" authorityYear="1903" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitoidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cirrhitoidea bimacula Jenkins 1903:489" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bimacula">bimacula</taxonomicName>
as a species of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Paracirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Paracirrhites</taxonomicName>
. He described 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:75A3E3A4-E289-4809-9A69-2CD2802702B8" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Amblycirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Amblycirrhitus hubbardi Schultz 1943:132" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hubbardi">hubbardi</taxonomicName>
as a new species in the genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A7B68FE2-7E5D-4D15-BFA4-EE2E8BD8F54C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Amblycirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Amblycirrhitus Gill 1862:105" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Amblycirrhitus</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="3">
Watanabe (1949) described 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:8095F6CC-F238-412C-89EA-58A9087C3364" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Serranocirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Serranocirrhitus latus Watanabe 1949:18" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="latus">Serranocirrhitus latus</taxonomicName>
as a new genus and species of cirrhitid fish from Okinawa.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="3">
In a review of western Indian Ocean 
<taxonomicName family="Cirrhitidae" pageNumber="3" rank="family">Cirrhitidae</taxonomicName>
, Smith (1951) created the genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:8AFD1869-8E1F-4D76-94F8-9387419C91DA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cirrhitops Smith 1951:(627) 637" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cirrhitops</taxonomicName>
for 
<taxonomicName authority="Lacepède, 1803" authorityName="Lacepède" authorityYear="1803" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fasciatus">Cirrhites fasciatus Bennett</taxonomicName>
. He mistakenly listed 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:75A3E3A4-E289-4809-9A69-2CD2802702B8" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Amblycirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Amblycirrhitus hubbardi Schultz 1943:132" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hubbardi">Amblycirrhitus hubbardi Schultz</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fasciatus">fasciatus</taxonomicName>
. He also described 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:8BE7E6F6-576F-4824-9BA1-48C11F507E8A" authority="Smith, 1951" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1951" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Gymnocirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Gymnocirrhites Smith 1951:638" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Gymnocirrhites</taxonomicName>
as a new genus, with 
<taxonomicName authority="Lacepède, 1803" authorityName="Lacepède" authorityYear="1803" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="arcatus">Cirrhites arcatus Cuvier</taxonomicName>
as the type species, adding that it is allied to 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Paracirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Paracirrhites</taxonomicName>
but distinct on the basis of lacking scales on the gill membrane and on the snout before the nostrils.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="3">
Schultz in Schultz &amp; collaborators (1960) recognized 13 genera in the 
<taxonomicName family="Cirrhitidae" pageNumber="3" rank="family">Cirrhitidae</taxonomicName>
, including 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:2F6B48D5-B8C9-49E2-9393-87E1181F30DA" authority="Jordan, 1907" authorityName="Jordan" authorityYear="1907" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Isobuna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Isobuna Jordan 1907:158" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Isobuna</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:24979421-3FC5-48B6-B0B5-5B9EBAB16328" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Serranocirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Serranocirrhitus Watanabe 1949:17" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Serranocirrhitus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3C44979F-8863-4A9F-8276-923CD87238D8" authority="Jenkins, 1903" authorityName="Jenkins" authorityYear="1903" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitoidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cirrhitoidea Jenkins 1903:489" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cirrhitoidea</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:610A9D36-A6BE-46D2-9742-4B032894253B" authority="Schultz, 1943" authorityName="Schultz" authorityYear="1943" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Hughichthys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hughichthys Schultz 1943:131, 136" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hughichthys</taxonomicName>
(though indicating that 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CC926BD0-C0C7-4941-87D0-54080B379A74" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Neocirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Neocirrhites Castelnau 1873:101" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Neocirrhites</taxonomicName>
“appears to be related”), and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:8BE7E6F6-576F-4824-9BA1-48C11F507E8A" authority="Smith, 1951" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1951" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Gymnocirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Gymnocirrhites Smith 1951:638" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Gymnocirrhites</taxonomicName>
. He obviously had some doubt of the validity of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:8BE7E6F6-576F-4824-9BA1-48C11F507E8A" authority="Smith, 1951" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1951" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Gymnocirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Gymnocirrhites Smith 1951:638" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Gymnocirrhites</taxonomicName>
, stating that Smith (1951) “attaches too much value to the scaly gill membranes.” He noted that a specimen of 
<taxonomicName authority="Smith, 1951" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1951" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Gymnocirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="arcatus">G. arcatus</taxonomicName>
48 mm in SL lacks scales on the gill membranes, but a specimen of 100 mm SL has them. He left 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:5BF2B80F-9DD4-43F0-822F-2E04167F332E" authority="Jenkins, 1903" authorityName="Jenkins" authorityYear="1903" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitoidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cirrhitoidea bimacula Jenkins 1903:489" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bimacula">bimacula</taxonomicName>
in the genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3C44979F-8863-4A9F-8276-923CD87238D8" authority="Jenkins, 1903" authorityName="Jenkins" authorityYear="1903" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitoidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cirrhitoidea Jenkins 1903:489" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cirrhitoidea</taxonomicName>
and described a new species, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7953184B-FD9B-41D9-8B0F-8DC50FE578AE" authority="Jenkins, 1903" authorityName="Jenkins" authorityYear="1903" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitoidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cirrhitoidea sexfasciata Schultz 1960:257" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sexfasciata">sexfasciata</taxonomicName>
, in this genus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="3">
Randall (1963) reviewed the family, recognizing 10 genera and 34 species. He discussed 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:24979421-3FC5-48B6-B0B5-5B9EBAB16328" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Serranocirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Serranocirrhitus Watanabe 1949:17" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Serranocirrhitus</taxonomicName>
in a footnote, noting the following noncirrhitid characters: all the pectoral rays unbranched and none thickened, no teeth on the vomer, ctenoid scales, and the configuration of a pomacentrid. He included 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:2F6B48D5-B8C9-49E2-9393-87E1181F30DA" authority="Jordan, 1907" authorityName="Jordan" authorityYear="1907" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Isobuna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Isobuna Jordan 1907:158" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Isobuna</taxonomicName>
but stated that it differs from other cirrhitids in having 3 spines on the opercle instead of 2, ctenoid scales, and only 2 rows of scales above the lateral line. He recognized 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CC926BD0-C0C7-4941-87D0-54080B379A74" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Neocirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Neocirrhites Castelnau 1873:101" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Neocirrhites</taxonomicName>
as a valid genus with 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:610A9D36-A6BE-46D2-9742-4B032894253B" authority="Schultz, 1943" authorityName="Schultz" authorityYear="1943" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Hughichthys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hughichthys Schultz 1943:131, 136" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hughichthys</taxonomicName>
a synonym, placed 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:8BE7E6F6-576F-4824-9BA1-48C11F507E8A" authority="Smith, 1951" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1951" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Gymnocirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Gymnocirrhites Smith 1951:638" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Gymnocirrhites</taxonomicName>
in the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Paracirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Paracirrhites</taxonomicName>
, described 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CA98AA32-5CBA-419D-922A-D8D84AA880CE" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Isocirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Isocirrhitus Randall 1963:422" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Isocirrhitus</taxonomicName>
as a new genus for Schultz’ 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Isocirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sexfasciatus">sexfasciata</taxonomicName>
, put 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hubbardi">hubbardi</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:8AFD1869-8E1F-4D76-94F8-9387419C91DA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cirrhitops Smith 1951:(627) 637" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cirrhitops</taxonomicName>
, referred 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:6AD3621E-4DC7-4F31-A629-D987B190847D" authority="Gill, 1862" authorityName="Gill" authorityYear="1862" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cirrhitopsis Gill 1862:109" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cirrhitopsis</taxonomicName>
to the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A7B81F0C-1F8D-4339-A46A-3F2F625784D3" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Cirrhitichthys Bleeker 1857:3, 39" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cirrhitichthys</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Mowbray, 1927" authorityName="Mowbray" authorityYear="1927" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Pseudocirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudocirrhites</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A7B68FE2-7E5D-4D15-BFA4-EE2E8BD8F54C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Amblycirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Amblycirrhitus Gill 1862:105" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Amblycirrhitus</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="3">
Randall &amp; Heemstra (1978) reclassified the genera 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:24979421-3FC5-48B6-B0B5-5B9EBAB16328" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Serranocirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Serranocirrhitus Watanabe 1949:17" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Serranocirrhitus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:2F6B48D5-B8C9-49E2-9393-87E1181F30DA" authority="Jordan, 1907" authorityName="Jordan" authorityYear="1907" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Isobuna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Isobuna Jordan 1907:158" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Isobuna</taxonomicName>
in the subfamily Anthiinae of the Serranidae. That these two genera should have been placed in the 
<taxonomicName family="Cirrhitidae" pageNumber="3" rank="family">Cirrhitidae</taxonomicName>
is not as serious an error as it might seem. Jordan &amp; Evermann (1898) wrote with respect to the cirrhitoid fishes, “This family should apparently be placed among the Percoidea near the Serranidae....This group agrees with the Percoidea in most respects, the chief external difference lying in the form of the pectorals,...” They quoted 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Günther">Guenther</normalizedToken>
’s description of the skeleton of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Paracirrhites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="forsteri">Paracirrhites forsteri</taxonomicName>
, adding, “Dr. Boulenger finds that the skeleton has much in common (with the Serranidae)”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="3">
In 1969 the author collected 32 specimens of an undescribed species of cirrhitid from Easter Island that appeared to represent a new genus. The following year he collected two more specimens from Pitcairn Island. Unaware of this material, Lavenberg &amp; 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Yañez">Yanez</normalizedToken>
(1972) described the species as 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="wilhelmi">Cirrhitus wilhelmi</taxonomicName>
from one specimen from Easter Island.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="3">Kunio Amaoka requested specimens of the various genera of cirrhitid fishes from the Bishop Museum for a graduate student who planned a phylogenetic study of the family. Specimens were sent, including ones from Easter Island. The student did not complete the study, and the specimens were recently returned by Dr. Amaoka.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="4">
The present study has confirmed that the Easter Island - Pitcairn specimens of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="wilhelmi">wilhelmi</taxonomicName>
represent a new genus. The investigation of other cirrhitids currently placed in 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cirrhitidae" genus="Cirrhitus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cirrhitus</taxonomicName>
has revealed two more species that clearly require placement in new monotypic genera. The three new genera are described below after the revised generic key of the family.
</paragraph>
